  ('5cdefd7f-b1a8-594a-9c27-a4e657e5fdde', 'THE HAMPTON TRUST (HAMPSHIRE AND THE ISLE OF WIGHT)', 'Charity', 'Ashurst Lodge, Lyndhurst Road, SOUTHAMP, Norfolk', 'Norfolk', 'https://www.hamptontrust.org.uk', 25, 1709727, 'FY ending 2025-03-31; Charity Commission latest income', 5, 'Focusing on early intervention/preventative programmes across all ages to build resilience, disrupt patterns and break the cycle of abuse, tackling the root cause of domestic abuse and supporting victims and survivors, through tailored interventions to individuals committing abuse against their family. Providing visionary rehabilitation programmes for individuals in the criminal justice system.', 'Medium', '2026-06-24', 'primary', '', 'Chief Executive', 'info@hamptontrust.org.uk', '02380001061', 'https://register-of-charities.charitycommission.gov.uk/en/charity-search/-/charity-details/1055209/full-print', 'https://www.hamptontrust.org.uk', ARRAY['children'], ARRAY['children'], 'MEETING PREP — THE HAMPTON TRUST (HAMPSHIRE AND THE ISLE OF WIGHT) (Children, youth & families)

WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
Focusing on early intervention/preventative programmes across all ages to build resilience, disrupt patterns and break the cycle of abuse, tackling the root cause of domestic abuse and supporting victims and survivors, through tailored interventions to individuals committing abuse against their family. Providing visionary rehabilitation programmes for individuals in the criminal justice system.

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
Ashurst Lodge, Lyndhurst Road, SOUTHAMP, Norfolk, Norfolk. ~25 staff; income on record £1,709,727.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Blend: training + workflow review

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Children and family services span casework, safeguarding, referrals and programme reporting.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Youth charities often juggle CRM or case tools with heavy manual reporting to councils and funders. AI for programme summaries and parent communications is emerging but needs clear policy.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA is not the right lead for safeguarding case management — prioritise policy, training, and referral workflow clarity.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
THE HAMPTON TRUST (HAMPSHIRE AND THE ISLE OF WIGHT) shows children, youth & families delivery with material admin load — Cut grant reporting prep without changing your case system

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Cut grant reporting prep without changing your case system
• AI policy workshop for staff working with children and families
• Map referral and enrolment bottlenecks across programmes

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
• What systems are in use today — and where do spreadsheets or email still carry the load?
• Has anyone been asked to explore AI, and is there a policy or governance concern?
• What would success look like in 90 days for the operations or programmes team?

